Templars are divine warrior-healers who synthesize Paladin advance doctrine with Priest restoration capability.
The title descends from the Solar Court's temple-guard auxiliaries who stood between battle-clergy and ceremonial ministry.
The synthesis was forced during the Violet Compact's founding years when garrison forces were too few to maintain separate Paladin and Priest functions.
Practitioners who cross-trained discovered that integration at depth produced qualitatively different results than minimum-coverage cross-training.
Combat role is hybrid divine melee and healer, shifting between offensive and restorative functions as conditions require.
Key contribution: integrating healing with status-cure functions in a single working, eliminating sequential application gaps.
The tradition holds that advance and restoration are not two functions requiring two specialists but one function.
This is a remort class requiring depth in both Paladin and Priest traditions.
The Violet Compact absorbed the resulting Corps as a sanctioned order.
